%description
The launcher scripts, native binaries and libraries needed to run the 
Pipeline client programs under Windows XP.  

This RPM should be installed on the same Linux file server as the main 
"pipeline" RPM.  Note that this RPM does not contain the required Java 
classes or data files needed to run the Pipeline client applications.
These resources are accessed over a network share using the path supplied
to the Windows Root Install Directory (--win-root-dir option) to 
plconfig(1) during Pipeline configuration process.

Windows machines must install the PipelineJobManager service locally in
order to participate in procesing jobs for the Pipeline queue.  You must
first run the Windows installer for the Job Manager service which can be
found here:

  @WIN_ROOT_INST_DIR@/Windows/services/PipelineJobManager.msi

This will install a Windows service wrapper program and a pair of 
utilities for installing and uninstalling the program as a Windows 
service.  Once the service is installed, you must also start it before it
can begin processing jobs using:

  Control Panel -> Administrative Tools -> Services

